{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645315","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645315"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:15:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18105"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18105","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18105"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10819"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78262"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10819","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10819"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18105"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63670"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25183"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25186"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26851"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78262","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78262"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThere are a number of muscles in the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is located in this compartment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anconeus","Brachialis","Brachioradialis","Supinator","Triceps brachii"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrachialis\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is located in the anterior compartment of the arm and is primarily responsible for flexing the elbow joint. It lies deep to the biceps brachii and is a major flexor of the forearm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrachioradialis\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the forearm and is involved in flexing the elbow, particularly when the forearm is in a mid-pronated position. It is not part of the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etriceps brachii\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the posterior compartment of the arm and is responsible for extending the elbow joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanconeus\u003C/strong\u003E is a small muscle located near the elbow that assists in elbow extension and stabilisation. It is not part of the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esupinator\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the forearm and is responsible for supinating the forearm, turning the palm upwards. It is not part of the anterior compartment of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The brachialis muscle is located in the anterior compartment of the arm and is primarily responsible for flexing the elbow.","The brachioradialis muscle is located in the forearm and is involved in flexing the elbow, especially when the forearm is in a mid-pronated position."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. P